Name: AdministrativeGender
Title: AdministrativeGender
Descriptino: The gender of a person used for administrative purposes.

Name: BundleType
Title: BundleType
Descriptino: Indicates the purpose of a bundle - how it is intended to be used.

Name: PracticeSettingCodeValueSet
Title: Practice Setting Code Value Set
Descriptino: This is the code representing the clinical specialty of the clinician or provider who interacted with, treated, or provided a service to/for the patient. The value set used for clinical specialty has been limited by HITSP to the value set reproduced from HITSP C80 Table 2-149 Clinical Specialty Value Set Definition.

Name: CommonTags
Title: Common Tags
Descriptino: Common Tag Codes defined by FHIR project

Name: DaysOfWeek
Title: DaysOfWeek
Descriptino: The days of the week.

Name: HTTPVerb
Title: HTTPVerb
Descriptino: HTTP verbs (in the HTTP command line). See [HTTP rfc](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231) for details.

Name: Identifier Type Codes
Title: IdentifierType
Descriptino: A coded type for an identifier that can be used to determine which identifier to use for a specific purpose.

Name: IdentifierUse
Title: IdentifierUse
Descriptino: Identifies the purpose for this identifier, if known .

Name: CommonLanguages
Title: Common Languages
Descriptino: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

Name: LinkType
Title: LinkType
Descriptino: The type of link between this patient resource and another patient resource.

Name: Marital Status Codes
Title: MaritalStatus
Descriptino: This value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate the marital status of a person.

Name: Mime Types
Title: MimeType
Descriptino: This value set includes all possible codes from BCP-13 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp13)

Name: PatientContactRelationship
Title: Patient Contact Relationship
Descriptino: The nature of the relationship between the patient and the contact person.

Name: ProcedurePerformerRoleCodes
Title: Procedure Performer Role Codes
Descriptino: This example value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate a role of a procedure performer.

Name: PractitionerRole
Title: Practitioner role
Descriptino: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the role of a Practitioner.

Name: QuestionnaireAnswerCodes
Title: Questionnaire Answer Codes
Descriptino: Example list of codes for answers to questions. (Not complete or necessarily appropriate.)

Name: QuestionnaireResponseStatus
Title: QuestionnaireResponseStatus
Descriptino: Lifecycle status of the questionnaire response.

Name: RequestPriority
Title: Request priority
Descriptino: The clinical priority of a diagnostic order.

Name: ResourceType
Title: ResourceType
Descriptino: One of the resource types defined as part of this version of FHIR.

Name: SearchEntryMode
Title: SearchEntryMode
Descriptino: Why an entry is in the result set - whether it's included as a match or because of an _include requirement, or to convey information or warning information about the search process.

Name: All Security Labels
Title: SecurityLabels
Descriptino: A single value set for all security labels defined by FHIR.

Name: SignatureTypeCodes
Title: Signature Type Codes
Descriptino: The Digital Signature Purposes, an indication of the reason an entity signs a document. This is included in the signed information and can be used when determining accountability for various actions concerning the document. Examples include: author, transcriptionist/recorder, and witness.

Name: TaskIntent
Title: TaskIntent
Descriptino: Distinguishes whether the task is a proposal, plan or full order.

Name: USCoreDocumentReferenceType
Title: US Core DocumentReference Type
Descriptino: The US Core DocumentReference Type Value Set includes all LOINC values whose SCALE is "Doc" in the LOINC database and the HL7 v3 Code System NullFlavor concept 'unknown'

Name: CDexPOUCodes
Title: CDex Purpose of Use Value Set
Descriptino: The set of purpose of use (POU) codes for requesting data. This code set is composed of [FHIR core Purpose of Use security labels](http://hl7.org/fhir/security-labels.html#core) and additional codes defined by this Guide.

Name: CDexClaimUseCodes
Title: CDex Claim Use Value Set
Descriptino: The purpose of a Claim resource and the reason for attachments. It includes the codes "preauthorization" and "claim".

Name: CDexDataRequestTaskCode
Title: CDex Data Request Task Code Value Set
Descriptino: Codes used to identify the type of data request. It includes the codes “data-request-query”, “data-request-code”, and “data-request-questionnaire”.

Name: CDexIdentifierTypes
Title: CDex Identifier Types Value Set
Descriptino: Identifier types for providers and organizations. It includes the codes “TAX” and “NPI”.

Name: CDexLOINCAttachmentCodesValueSet
Title: CDex LOINC Attachment Codes Value Set
Descriptino: This value set includes LOINC terms that can be sent by a payer as part of an HL7 attachment request for additional information. It has been curated by the HL7 Payer/Provider Information Exchange (PIE) Work Group.  More information about using LOINC in HIPAA attachments and the source of this value set can be found at [LOINC Attahments](https://loinc.org/attachments/).

Name: CDexPWK01AttachmentReportTypeCodeValueSet
Title: CDex PWK01 Attachment Report Type Code Value Set
Descriptino: In addition to using LOINC attachment codes, a payer may request for additional information from the provider to support a prior authorization request using X12's PWK01 Attachment Report Type Code.  Note that the PWK01 codes will not be published in due to X12 IP restrictions.

Name: CDexWorkQueueCodes
Title: CDex Work Queue Value Set
Descriptino: The set work queue tags that the provider may use in their workflow to process requests. This code set is composed of codes defined by this Guide.

Name: HRexTaskStatus
Title: HRex Task Status ValueSet
Descriptino: The set of task codes allowed for use in HRex data request tasks

Name: PASTaskCodes
Title: PAS Task Codes
Descriptino: The code for the task that is request additional information.
